channel.description:
[u][b]Introduction[/b][/u]

Moparscape member relaxlawl released a pretty bad (not even functional) dwarf multicannon system about two years ago. I took it and made it functional, cleaned it, documented it, and added lots of new features that previously were not there.

Some of my code may be different from what you use, figure it out and if you really can't then send me a pm or post below.

I did this on Project Insanity, so decent programmers shouldn't have a problem getting this to work on similar derivatives.




[u][b]Features[/b][/u]

[ul][li]Cannon loading, and reloading[/li]
[li]Single and multiplayer firing support[/li]
[li]Selective mob firing based on the cannons rotation[/li]
[li]You cannot fire or pickup another player's cannon[/li]
[li]You cannot build a cannon within a certain amount of tiles of another cannon[/li]
[li]You cannot build more than one cannon[/li]
[li]On logout the cannon is stopped and returned to the inventory[/li]
[li]On death the cannon is stopped[/li][/ul]


Probably more, can't remember.




[u][b]The Tutorial[/b][/u]

Ok lets get this show on the road.

Firstly, add these two classes. Almost everything is explained in the documentation, seriously. You'd have to be illiterate to not understand what's going on. Pastebin was used to compensate for the character limit.


[i]DwarfCannon.java[/i]

http://pastebin.com/hHuwBZHB


[i]MultiCannonObject.java[/i]

[code=java]package server.rs2.players;

import server.world.Position;
import server.world.objects.Objects;

/**
 * Represents a dwarf multicannon that will be placed in the rs2 world. We
 * extend {@link Objects} so that we can inherit all the traits of a regular
 * Object, plus add our own traits.
 * 
 * @author lare96
 */
public class MultiCannonObject extends Objects {

    /**
     * The player in control of this dwarf multicannon. This field is very
     * important because it ensures that no one else can fire, or pickup this
     * cannon.
     */
    private Player owner;

    /**
     * Construct a new dwarf multicannon
     */
    public MultiCannonObject(int id, Player owner) {
        super(id, new Position(owner.absX, owner.absY, owner.heightLevel), 0, 10);
        this.setOwner(owner);
    }

    /**
     * @return the owner
     */
    public Player getOwner() {
        return owner;
    }

    /**
     * @param owner
     *            the owner to set
     */
    public void setOwner(Player owner) {
        this.owner = owner;
    }
}[/code]



First we have to instance the class per player, so open up your [i]Player[/i] class and add this

[code=java]private DwarfCannon cannon = new DwarfCannon(this);

    /**
     * @return the cannon
     */
    public DwarfCannon getCannon() {
        return cannon;
    } [/code]



Second, we have to make it so that when we are setting up the cannon we won't move. In your [i]Walking[/i] class, at the beginning of the [i]processPacket[/i] method, add

[code=java]        if (c.getCannon().isBulding()) {
            return;
        } [/code]



Next, we have to make it so we can fire and pickup the cannon. In [i]ActionHandler[/i], in the [i]firstClickObject[/i] method, add

[code=java]            case 6:
                player.getCannon().shoot(new Position(player.objectX, player.objectY, player.heightLevel));
                break; [/code]

and in the [i]secondClickObject[/i] method, add

[code=java]            case 6:
                player.getCannon().pickup(new Position(player.objectX, player.objectY, player.heightLevel));
                break;[/code]



Then, we have to make it so on death the cannon stops. In [i]PlayerAssistant[/i], at the end of the [i]giveLife()[/i] method, add

[code=java]            MultiCannonObject o = getCannon().cannon;

            if (o != null) {
                Position p = new Position(o.getPosition().getX(), o.getPosition().getY(), o.getPosition().getZ());
                getCannon().pickup(p);
            }
[/code]



Next, we have to make it so on logout the cannon is stopped. In [i]Player[/i], somewhere in the [i]logout()[/i] method add

[code=java]            MultiCannonObject o = getCannon().cannon;

            if (o != null) {
                Position p = new Position(o.getPosition().getX(), o.getPosition().getY(), o.getPosition().getZ());
                getCannon().pickup(p);
            }[/code]



And finally, add this class, and these methods if you don't have them. We need the methods to fire the cannonball projectiles, and we need the class to represent a [i]Position[/i] point. 

[code=java]    public void createPlayersObjectAnim(int X, int Y, int animationID, int tileObjectType, int orientation) {
        try {
            player.getOutStream().createFrame(85);
            player.getOutStream().writeByteC(Y - (player.mapRegionY * 8));
            player.getOutStream().writeByteC(X - (player.mapRegionX * 8));
            int x = 0;
            int y = 0;
            player.getOutStream().createFrame(160);
            player.getOutStream().writeByteS(((x & 7) << 4) + (y & 7));// tiles
                                                                       // away
            // - could
            // just send 0
            player.getOutStream().writeByteS((tileObjectType << 2) + (orientation & 3));
            player.getOutStream().writeWordA(animationID);// animation id
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    public void objectAnim(int X, int Y, int animationID, int tileObjectType, int orientation) {
        for (Player p : PlayerHandler.players) {
            if (p != null) {

                if (p.distanceToPoint(X, Y) <= 25) {
                    p.getPA().createPlayersObjectAnim(X, Y, animationID, tileObjectType, orientation);
                }
            }
        }
    }
 [/code]


[i]Position.java[/i]

[code=java]package server.world;

/**
 * Represents any position point in the rs2 world
 *
 * @author lare96
 */
public class Position {

    /**
     * Fields that repesent the x, y, and z coordinates
     */
    private int x, y, z;

    /**
     * Constructs a new Position with the specified coordinates.
     *
     * @param x
     *            the X coordinate
     * @param y
     *            the Y coordinate
     * @param z
     *            the Z coordinate
     */
    public Position(int x, int y, int z) {
        setX(x);
        setY(y);
        setZ(z);
    }

    /**
     * Constructs a new Position with the specified coordinates. and the height
     * as 0
     *
     * @param x
     *            the X coordinate
     * @param y
     *            the Y coordinate
     * @param z
     *            the Z coordinate
     */
    public Position(int x, int y) {
        setX(x);
        setY(y);
        setZ(0);
    }

    /**
     * Sets the X coordinate.
     *
     * @param x
     *            the X coordinate
     */
    public void setX(int x) {
        this.x = x;
    }

    /**
     * Gets the X coordinate.
     *
     * @return the X coordinate
     */
    public int getX() {
        return x;
    }

    /**
     * Sets the Y coordinate.
     *
     * @param y
     *            the Y coordinate
     */
    public void setY(int y) {
        this.y = y;
    }

    /**
     * Gets the Y coordinate.
     *
     * @return the Y coordinate
     */
    public int getY() {
        return y;
    }

    /**
     * Sets the Z coordinate.
     *
     * @param z
     *            the Z coordinate
     */
    public void setZ(int z) {
        this.z = z;
    }

    /**
     * Gets the Z coordinate.
     *
     * @return the Z coordinate.
     */
    public int getZ() {
        return z;
    }

    /**
     * Checks if the position is within a another position
     */
    public boolean withinDistance(Position position, int distance) {
        if (this.getZ() != position.getZ())
            return false;

        return Math.abs(position.getX() - this.getX()) <= distance && Math.abs(position.getY() - this.getY()) <= distance;
    }

    /**
     * Checks if the position is viewable from another position
     */
    public boolean isViewableFrom(Position position) {
        if (this.getZ() != position.getZ())
            return false;

        return Math.abs(position.getX() - this.getX()) <= 14 && Math.abs(position.getY() - this.getY()) <= 14;
    }

    /**
     * Checks if this position is equal to another position
     */
    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object anObject) {
        if (!(anObject instanceof Position)) {
            return false;
        }

        Position p = (Position) anObject;

        if (p == this) {
            return true;
        }

        if (p.getX() == this.getX() && p.getY() == this.getY() && p.getZ() == this.getZ()) {
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    /**
     * Returns the current position in a string literal
     */
    @Override
    public String toString() {
        return "[x: " + this.getX() + " || y: " + this.getY() + " || z " + this.getZ() + "]";
    }

    /**
     * Returns a duplicate position of the instance calling this method
     */
    @Override
    public Object clone() {
        return new Position(x, y, z);
    }
}[/code]

And that's pretty much it! Everything else is handled in the [i]DwarfCannon[/i] class.




